// Semantic direction:
// ekstern_minne algorithms minimize em_blokk_overføringer (disk I/O) rather than comparisons.
// em_blokk_størrelse is typically 4–64 KB matching the OS page or disk sector size.
// b_tre orders its keys so any page-sized node fits in one disk block — optimal I/O.
// bt_min_nøkler = ⌈bt_orden/2⌉ - 1 guarantees the tree stays balanced after deletion.
// bt_split divides an overfull node into two and promotes the median key to the parent.
// bt_merge_bt combines an underfull node with a sibling when both are below minimum.
// b_pluss_tre stores all values at bpt_bladnode level; internal nodes hold routing keys only.
// bpt_bladlenke chains all leaves for efficient bpt_rekkevidde_søk without backtracking.
// bpt_bulk_last builds the tree bottom-up from sorted input — much faster than repeated inserts.
// buffer_tre (Buffered B-tree) stores updates in node buffers to batch I/O (Arge et al.).
// bet_buffer_per_node defers propagation until a buffer fills, reducing write amplification.
// es_k_vei_merge merges k sorted runs using a priority queue; keeps k disk pages in memory.
// es_dobbel_buffer_es overlaps CPU merge work with disk I/O using double buffering.
// replacement_selection produces longer initial runs than naive sorting by using a tournament tree.
// co_van_emde_boas_layout arranges a static tree in memory so every subtree is cache-friendly.
// co_fringe_søk achieves O((n/B) log_B n) block transfers — optimal for search trees.
// rtree_mbr is the minimum bounding rectangle for all spatial objects in a node.
// str_bulk_last (Sort-Tile-Recursive) builds R-trees with excellent spatial locality.

// Primitive flow:
// B-tre søk: les rot fra disk -> sjekk nøkler -> finn riktig barn-peker
//   les barn fra disk -> gjenta til bladnode -> returner verdi
//   I/O-kostnad: O(log_B n) blokk-overføringer
// ekstern sortering N elementer, M minne:
//   fase 1: les M bytes -> sorter i minne -> skriv til diskfil (N/M kjøringer)
//   fase 2: k-vei merge: les én side per kjøring -> merge med prio-kø
//   -> skriv til utdatafil
//   I/O: O(N/B * log_{M/B}(N/B)) blokk-overføringer
// cache-oblivious matmul: rekursivt del A, B, C i fire kvadranter
//   8 rekursive kall -> cache-linje lokalitet emerger automatisk
//   ingen eksplisitt blokkstørrelse — optimalt for alle cache-nivåer

// This defines external memory algorithms: B-tree with split/merge/rotate, B+-tree with
// bulk loading, buffered B-trees, external merge sort with replacement selection, cache-
// oblivious matrix multiplication and VEB layout, and R-tree bulk loading.
